	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Spectre Games in Oasis- Povar</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=555240" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Sephryna writes:
<blockquote><font color="beige">
Greetings, all.  I was travelling to Oasis, to collect a few kills and some Gator meat, when a giggling was heard across the land.  Lo and behold, a few moments later, two young spectres, Mirtly and Spirtly showed up.  They seem intent on playing a game of Tag...but apparently not many people realized how spectres play tag.  They liked to hit you a few times, then run...well, its no fair when they are it, and many of the people went after them.  After a while, everyone calmed down to talk, and we discovered that today was Mirtly's birthday.  His parents had finally let him leave spectre island.  Well, we played tag and hide and go seek, then they had to leave after a while.  But some mean people chased after them...I hope they are ok...Mirtly seemed to like games...

   Later that nite, a wailing was heard and the sky turned red...  Mom and Dad spectre screamed out to the area, that we would pay for the deaths of their children... I tried to explain to them that we played games...but parents can be rather stubborn.  After a bit, many adventurers showed up, and many tried to take on the whole spectre family... Mom, Dad, and about 30 brothers and sisters.   Soon the adventurers rushed the island, laying waste to the spectres and to the parents....I tried to help the parents out and get the meanies to stop hurting them, but I am only one wizard...  Soon after the death of the parents, and orphaning of the children...the skies returned to normal, and all departed.
<P>
/ooc  I think the event was rather well executed.  A lower level game, and then a much higher level game later on... As usual, higher level peeps think with the swords and not with the heads...so they attack first.  I think more would of happened had we searched for the missing children.  
<P>
  A few rewards were handed out...I recieved a nice gift from Mirtly...as savants cap.  Others got 3agi rings, and a 3sta necklace.  The reward I heard from the other event was a Erudite Paladin only necklace.  I hope to see the little bugger of a spectre again....
<P>
Sephryna<br>
16 wizard<br>
Circle of Shields<br>
Povar
</font></blockquote>
Screenshots of the event:
<p>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=555243">Screenshot 1</a><br>
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=555244">Screenshot 2</a>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
