			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				From what the poster wrote, it sounded like the kid specters were *low level* -- meaning they probably didn't kill those they tagged.  Now, a pissed of set of parents and family members would hit harder, and to kill, especially had the kids been murdered.<BR>
<BR>
Hit a couple times and run away doesn't sound too painful to me, tells me the victims survived the tag.<BR>
<BR>
Aside from that... It doesn't take being high level to find people who want to kill all NPCs involved in GM events.  A lvl 1-30 character with GM killing mentality will take swings at the NPCs as likely as a higher level person, they probably just won't connect as often, or as hard.<BR>
<BR>
On another note...the event obviously wasn't intended to further the story of Norrath, so the GMs expected and hoped the kiddie specters would die, so they could pull out their large family of Spectre Wrath.  It sounded like a well thought out, enjoyable event for both tiers of levels (low-mid, and mid-high).  I wish all the servers could have these kinds of events more often, unfortunately, Legends appears to be the only set that'll get ongoing, consistent GM events. :(
				</font>
